    <datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="245">
      <subfield code="a">Negative refractive index induced by percolation in disordered metamaterials</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="260">
      <subfield code="c">2017-03-03</subfield>
      <subfield code="t">published</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="300">
      <subfield code="a">5</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="520">
      <subfield code="a">An effective medium model is developed for disordered metamaterials containing a spatially random distribution of dielectric spheres. Similar to effective medium models for ordered metamaterials, this model predicts resonances in the effective permeability and permittivity arising from electric- and magnetic-dipole Mie resonances in the spheres. In addition, the model predicts a redshift of the electric resonance with increasing particle loading. Interestingly, when the particle loading exceeds the percolation threshold of 33%, the model predicts that the electric resonance overlaps with the magnetic resonance, resulting in a negative refractive index.</subfield>
      <subfield code="9">APS</subfield>
    </datafield>
